'''John Quenneville''' (born April 16, 1996) is a [[Canada|Canadian]] [[ice hockey]] player. He is currently playing in the [[Western Hockey League]] (WHL) with the [[Brandon Wheat Kings]]. Quenneville is rated as a top prospect<ref>[http://lastwordonsports.com/2014/05/14/2014-nhl-draft-profile-41-john-quenneville/ 2014 NHL Draft Profile #41: John Quenneville - Last Word On Sports<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> who is viewed as a possible first round selection in the [[2014 NHL Entry Draft]].<ref >[http://www.jacketscannon.com/2014/6/4/5778838/2014-nhl-draft-prospect-profile-30-john-quenneville 2014 NHL Draft Prospect Profile #30 - John Quenneville - The Cannon<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> 

Quenneville was selected by the [[Brandon Wheat Kings]] in the 3rd round (54th overall) of the 2011 WHL Bantam Draft.<ref>[http://www.wheatkings.com/article/season-to-continue-for-pair Season To Continue For Pair<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> He has played with the Brandon Wheat Kings since the [[2012<U+2013>13 WHL season]].<ref>[http://www.wheatkings.com/roster/bio/117937 Brandon Wheat Kings: #17 John Quenneville<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> 
==International==
As a 16-year-old he was chosen to compete with the Canada Pacific squad at the 2013 [[World U-17 Hockey Challenge]],<ref>{{cite news |last=Henderson |first=Rob |date=November 21, 2012 |title= John Quenneville |url= |newspaper=Brandon Sun |location= |publisher= |accessdate= }} </ref> and he helped [[Canada men's national under-18 ice hockey team|Team Canada]] capture the bronze medal at the [[2014 IIHF World U18 Championships]].<ref>[http://www.chl.ca/article/canada-wins-bronze-at-2014-world-u18 CHL Network: Canada wins Bronze at 2014 World U18<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

==Family==
His older brother Peter was drafted in the seventh round by the [[Columbus Blue Jackets]] in the [[2013 NHL Entry Draft]],<ref>[http://www.inlouwetrust.com/2014/5/6/5687196/john-quenneville-2014-nhl-draft-prospect-profile John Quenneville - 2014 NHL Draft Prospect Profile - In Lou We Trust<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and NHL head coach [[Joel Quenneville]] is his second cousin.<ref>[http://www.brandonsun.com/sports/local/quennevilles-role-grows-for-wheat-kings-180337331.html?path=/sports/local&id=180337331&sortBy=rank&viewAllComments=y Quenneville's role grows for Wheat Kings - Brandon Sun<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

